# Writing Style

- Never use the em dash character (Unicode U+2014) in code, comments, docstrings,
  README, UI labels, commit messages, or any project text.
- Use a hyphen-minus (`-`) instead, with spaces where needed for readability
  (e.g. `TuneAI - entry point` instead of an em dash between words).
- When editing existing files, replace any em dash with `-` before committing.
